        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>,<strong> curry powder</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to the softened onion and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>date & tamarind stock</strong> to the pan with the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and increase the heat to medium-high</p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the cauliflower is tender and the sauce has reduced to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>cauliflower, date & tamarind curry</strong></p>",
